abstract: The government said it did not export wheat gluten or any product that might have put poison in dog and cat food in the United States.
snippet: The government said it did not export wheat gluten or any product that might have put poison in dog and cat food in the United States.
lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI, April 5 — China said today that it had no record of exporting any agricultural products that could have tainted the pet food that has been linked to the deaths of cats and dogs in the United States.

headline.main: China Says It Had Nothing to Do With Tainted Pet Foods
